## Project-Specific Rules (voice-feishu)

These are layered on top of the four principles and are non-negotiable.

### Credentials
- Never commit secrets. Read from macOS Keychain via `keyring`, `service=voice-feishu`.
- Missing credentials → fail loud with a clear instruction. No silent fallbacks.

### CLI safety
- All **`lark-cli`** invocations go through `desktop/tools/lark_cli.py`.
- That module maintains a whitelist; out-of-whitelist commands are rejected.
- Destructive ops (send/approve/delete/modify) follow `--dry-run` → preview → confirm.

### Logging
- Each tool call writes one JSON line to `~/.voice-feishu/logs/tools.jsonl`:
  `{ts, tool, args, result, duration_ms, context, ok}`.
- Never log raw audio bytes or full API tokens; mask to last 4 chars.

### Phase boundaries
- Each Phase has a written Definition of Done in `docs/AGENTS.md`.
- Do not start a Phase before the prior Phase's DoD is met.
- Each Phase must include at least one runnable verification.

### Sub-agent boundaries
- A sub-agent must not modify files outside its declared scope in `docs/AGENTS.md`.
- If a sub-agent finds a needed change outside scope, it reports back; it does not silently expand scope.

### Python style
- Python 3.11+, type hints on all public functions.
- `ruff` + `mypy --strict` must pass. Match existing style when editing.
- Prefer `asyncio` over threads for I/O concurrency.
